<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Calamagrostis</i> <i>purpurascens</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the herbaceous and subshrub layers with <i>Achnatherum</i> <i>pinetorum</i>, <i>Calamagrostis</i> <i>canadensis</i>, <i>Carex</i> spp., <i>Elymus</i> <i>elymoides</i>, <i>Ericameria</i> <i>discoidea</i>, <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>ovalifolium</i>, <i>Festuca</i> spp., <i>Linanthus</i> <i>pungens</i>, <i>Minuartia</i> <i>nuttallii</i> and <i>Poa</i> spp. Emergent shrubs may be present at low cover, including <i>Ericameria</i> <i>parryi</i> var. <i>monocephala</i> or <i>Ribes</i> <i>cereum</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 80 cm; cover is open to continuous. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Calamagrostis purpurascens</i> scattered in small tufts and interspersed between subshrubs or matted perennial herbs such as <i>Ericameria parryi</i> var. <i>monocephala, Eriogonum ovalifolium, </i>and <i>Linanthus pungens</i> (Keeler-Wolf et al. 2003b).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Exposed rocky ridge tops and slopes with southern and western aspects that are nearly blown free of snow during the winter. Soils are well drained.  </div>
</div>

        
