<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Remarks</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Calamagrostis purpurascens </i>is an erect, densely tufted, perennial grass to 1 m tall. Old blades are persistent at the base of the plant, and the rhizomes are short and thick. Plants reproduce infrequently from seed when environmental conditions are favorable (Tesky 1992b). This circumpolar species grows at arctic and alpine elevations in North America and Asia. <br/>
<br/>
The alliance occurs scattered in alpine zones of British Columbia, California, Idaho, and Washington (NatureServe 2007a). It occurs in exposed rocky areas where snow scarcely accumulates and melts early (Sawyer and Keeler-Wolf 2007). </div>
</div>

    
	
	
