    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
        <h4 class="header">Regional Status</h4>
        
            <p>The range of <i>Calamagrostis purpurascens</i> includes the highest elevations of the Inyo Mountains (341Fb), Klamath Mountains (M261A), Southern Cascades (M261D), and Sweetwater and White mountains (341Dd, Dj).</p>
        

        <ul class="text">
        
            <li><b>Sierra Nevada</b> (M261Eo). Stands from Yosemite National Park (Keeler-Wolf et al. 2003b) and at Dana Plateau and Slate Creek on metamorphics (Major and Taylor 1977) characterize the alliance in California.</li>
        
        </ul>
    </div>


    
	
<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Management Considerations</h4>
	<div class="text"> Stands are found at high elevations in dry alpine areas, far from most human activities, but not protected from the effects of climate change. </div>
</div>

    

    

    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
